History.Time with Elisande:
{{Quote|That is why I brought these heroes, and the daughter of the Dark Sun.|Ausuriel to Graz'zt, when told she was powerless to stop him.}}
For a time during 1480s DR,{{ToD-time}} Ausuriel lived as a blind goat in a small village on an isle not too far from [[Phlan]].{{Cite adventurers league/Shadows over the Moonsea|15}}

Elisande and Ausuriel later moved to [[Phlan]], and remained there for a time, until the [[Cult of the Dragon]] took the city in a bloody coup.{{Cite adventurers league/Tyranny in Phlan|17}} The pair escaped from Phlan, and found a place to stay at [[Fort Iron]] in the [[Underdark]], near [[Mulmaster]].

Elisande and Ausuriel traveled across the Moonsea together. They briefly attended a celebration for Mielikki in the village of [[Elventree]] ''circa'' [[1486 DR]],{{Cite adventurers league/The Malady of Elventree|8}} and even traveled back to the Underdark, near the village of [[the Stop]].{{Cite adventurers league/Quelling the Horde|10}} 

Later in [[Sporedome]], the pair joined in on the planning of an assault on the [[drow]] city of [[Maerimydra]].{{Cite adventurers league/Assault on Maerimydra|11}} In fact, Elisande joined a group of [[adventurer]]s in their attack on the fortress, all the way to the [[Undying Temple]].{{Cite adventurers league/Assault on Maerimydra|46-47}} It was there that the pair helped prevent the Dark Prince [[Graz'zt]] from resisting a magical trap set up by [[Vizeran DeVir]] and [[Gromph Baenre]] that would trap the recently released [[demon lord]]s. It was there in the temple that Graz'zt revealed Ausuriel's true identity, just before Elisande gleefully stabbed the demon lord in the chest.{{Cite adventurers league/Assault on Maerimydra|46-47}}{{Cite adventurers league/Assault on Maerimydra|70}}

History.Shepherding Dara:
In the {{YearlinkName|1492}}, Ausuriel once again took the form of a goat, now named '''Clyde''', to join another of the god's chosen, [[Dara]] the young priestess of [[Ilmater]]. Ausuriel and the [[planetar]] [[Rinzel]]―who took the form of an elderly herder named Ghorin―accompanied Dara on her divine quest in the Realms.

After the city of [[Elturel]] was pulled down to the [[Nine Hells]], Dara, Ghorin, and Clyde (but mostly Dara) rallied a group of adventurers to save any innocents imperiled by the destruction. They helped the unfortunate Elturgardians join a refugee caravan to safety in the nearby city of [[Baldur's Gate]].{{Cite adventurers league/Escape from Elturgard|3-14}}

Once in Baldur's Gate, the trio went missing and the refugees they had saved became threatened by [[Gharizol]], a [[barbed devil]] who had been summoned to the city by a [[Cult of Zariel|group of cultists]]. Dara's adventurer friends managed to defeat the devil and save the refugees, some of whom it was revealed were descendants of Elturel's famous cavalry, the [[Hellriders]].{{Cite adventurers league/Day of the Devil|6-8}} Ausuriel and Rinsel then appeared with Dara, and revealed their true identities to the adventures. The angels wanted find heroes brave enough to accompany Dara and her divine quest, to find the lost [[soul]]s of Hellriders that perished during [[Hellriders#History|the Ride]] into the Hells and free them from imprisonment in [[Avernus]].
